</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="88" pageNumber="89" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="88.[151,1437,1682,2033]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,325,1935,1961]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">Host plant</emphasis>
. Unknown. Many of the specimens from Odaesan Mts., 
<collectingCountry box="[965,1108,1935,1961]" name="South Korea" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">South Korea</collectingCountry>
, were swept from the foliage of 
<taxonomicName box="[182,291,1971,1997]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Padus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[182,252,1971,1997]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">Padus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[305,417,1971,1997]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Rosaceae</taxonomicName>
), which may possibly be a host plant of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="89" lastPageNumber="90" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="88.[151,1437,1682,2033]" box="[199,1437,2007,2033]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,2007,2033]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species is well characterized by the large elongate glabrous ovipositor sheath appendage (
<figureCitation box="[1391,1437,2007,2033]" captionStart="FIGURE 77" captionStartId="166.[151,250,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-26@166.[151,1435,181,1845]" captionTargetPageId="166" captionText="FIGURE 77. Pamphilius heecheonparki, female, Korea (paratype) – (a) dorsally, (b) lateroventrally, (c) head &amp; thorax dorsally, (d) head &amp; thorax ventrolaterally, (e) face, (f) antenna, (g) claw, (h) sawsheath laterally." pageId="88" pageNumber="89">Fig.</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="89.[151,1437,150,501]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">
77h) in the female and the anchor-like penis valve (
<figureCitation box="[721,802,150,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="52.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[191,1396,181,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-26@52.[191,1396,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="FIGURE 11. Key to Pamphilius species 6" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
: 61a) in the male. 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[1005,1200,150,176]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" pagination="225 - 252" refId="ref76684" refString="Shinohara, A. (1998) Pamphilius albopictus (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae) and its close relatives. Bulletin of the National Science Museum, Tokyo, Series A, 24, 225 - 252." type="journal article" year="1998">Shinohara (1998)</bibRefCitation>
included this species in his 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kirby" authorityYear="1882" box="[219,363,186,212]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albopictus">
<emphasis box="[219,363,186,212]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">P. albopictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Malaise" authorityYear="1931" box="[552,637,186,212]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vafer">
<emphasis box="[552,637,186,212]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">P. vafer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group but later he (2002b) proposed the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1998" box="[1094,1286,186,212]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heecheonparki">
<emphasis box="[1094,1286,186,212]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">P. heecheonparki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup for this species alone.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="89.[151,1437,150,501]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">
In our molecular analysis, the six available COI sequences of this species from 
<collectingCountry box="[1084,1224,258,285]" name="South Korea" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">South Korea</collectingCountry>
were identical and the maximum intraspecific 
<emphasis box="[462,476,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">p</emphasis>
-distance among the six NaK sequences was 0.2%. The nearest neighbour was 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Takeuchi" authorityYear="1930" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kamikochensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">P. kamikochensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(a member of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kirby" authorityYear="1882" box="[492,636,330,356]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albopictus">
<emphasis box="[492,636,330,356]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">P. albopictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup), diverging by a minimum of 3.2% in the COI analysis and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="masao">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">P. masao</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(members of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Malaise" authorityYear="1931" box="[423,509,366,392]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vafer">
<emphasis box="[423,509,366,392]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">P. vafer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup) by a minimum of 0.5% in the NaK analysis. In the COI tree (
<figureCitation box="[1325,1423,366,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 148" captionStartId="235.[151,250,1827,1851]" captionTargetBox="[157,1427,198,1794]" captionTargetId="figure-19@235.[151,1436,181,1803]" captionTargetPageId="235" captionText="FIGURE 148. Condensed ML tree based on CO1 gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius vafer group, part 1." pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Fig. 148</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1998" box="[151,344,402,428]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heecheonparki">
<emphasis box="[151,344,402,428]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">P. heecheonparki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was retrieved as the sister group of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kirby" authorityYear="1882" box="[747,891,402,428]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albopictus">
<emphasis box="[747,891,402,428]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">P. albopictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Takeuchi" authorityYear="1930" box="[921,1111,402,428]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kamikochensis">
<emphasis box="[921,1111,402,428]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">P. kamikochensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara &amp; Taeger" authorityYear="2007" box="[1141,1224,402,428]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leleji">
<emphasis box="[1141,1224,402,428]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">P. leleji</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 89% UFBoot support, whereas in the NaK tree (
<figureCitation box="[527,621,438,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 161" captionStartId="246.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[177,1403,189,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-26@246.[171,1417,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="246" captionText="FIGURE 161. Condensed ML tree based on NaK gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius vafer group, part 2." pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Fig. 161</figureCitation>
) 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1998" box="[636,827,438,464]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heecheonparki">
<emphasis box="[636,827,438,464]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">P. heecheonparki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was sister to the cluster of 
<taxonomicName box="[1123,1292,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stramineipes">
<emphasis box="[1123,1292,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">P. stramineipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName box="[1320,1436,438,464]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="togashii">
<emphasis box="[1320,1436,438,464]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">P. togashii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(with only 58% UFBoot support) with very low UFBoot value of 42%.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
